As of my last update in October 2023, Google Maps does not have a specific "time travel" endpoint in its API documentation. While Google does offer various features and APIs for street view imagery, such as the Street View Static API or the Street View Service in the Maps JavaScript API, these typically return the imagery of a location as it exists at a specific date. 

However, Google does capture historical imagery, and you can access different dates of imagery through the Google Maps interface if you're using Street View. To access this in a programmatic way could be somewhat limited.

### Example using Google Maps JavaScript API

This example demonstrates how to integrate Google Maps and retrieve Street View imagery, but note that this code will not allow you to toggle between historical imagery programmatically as there is no dedicated API for that as of now. If Google adds this functionality, you'd likely find it under their existing APIs with relevant documentation.

Here's how you can set up a basic Google Maps instance with Street View:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Street View Example</title>
    <script src="https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?key=YOUR_API_KEY"></script>
    <style>
        #map {
            height: 500px;
            width: 100%;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="map"></div>
    <script>
        function initMap() {
            // The location of the desired point
            const location = { lat: 40.6892, lng: -74.0445 }; // Example: Statue of Liberty

            // Create a map centered on the desired location
            const map = new google.maps.Map(document.getElementById("map"), {
                zoom: 14,
                center: location,
            });

            // Create a Street View panorama
            const panorama = new google.maps.StreetViewPanorama(
                document.getElementById("map"), {
                    position: location,
                    pov: {
                        heading: 165,
                        pitch: 0,
                    },
                    zoom: 1,
                }
            );

            map.setStreetView(panorama);
        }

        // Initialize the map
        window.onload = initMap;
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Important Notes:
- **API Key**: Replace `YOUR_API_KEY` with your actual Google Maps API key.
- **Historical Street View**: As of my last training cut-off, while Google supports viewing historical street view images, there's no public API endpoint to retrieve specific dates programmatically.
- **Legal Considerations**: Be sure to adhere to Google's terms of service when using their APIs and displaying data.

### Future considerations
For the most up-to-date capabilities, check the official [Google Maps Platform documentation](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation) regularly. Google may add new features or endpoints that allow more advanced functionalities like "time travel" in their map services.
